title: ACCOLADES The Writer Never Noticed
body_text:
Throughout the countless years of semi-embellished and exaggerated ECD stories, there are extremely rare instances when even the almighty Writer fails to realize the true magnitude of certain situations.
It's no secret that Diana DiBuccio and Lauren Stopa have a legitimate claim as the sport's most famed and iconic females. Their legacies are built on career longevity and incomparable success as well as the admiration and recognition of those far beyond the ECD nation.
How many appearances? A "grand slam" what? If you're not sure or sold on the forthcoming DiBuccio-Stopa confrontation, let this in-depth documentation do the talking:
